values:
Agh!  I have to do a cheer, a chant, and a dance.  I am so freaked out.  I look like a damn cheerleader.  Hee Hee.
2:45 PM....

Dun dun dun....

Cheerleading is hard!

I can not believe I am trying to do this.  Agh.

Only four more days...

Cheerleading Tryouts Day One!

Feeling like crap...oh look this is what a lack of smoking does to you!

Ugh, now I know why people never quit!

I have been filling out applications for next year.

Video Broadcast - Editor (Screw Josh, that job is MINE!  I'll kill him with a knife...)
Cheerleading...
Scedules for next year.

To think that I am going to be a Senior, that really scares the life out of me...can you believe it?

Well I better get back to work on filling this paper work out.

Oh yes, Cheerleading Meeting...AFTER SCHOOL TODAY!!!!!!!!! =D YaY!

You know when you can get all the sleep in the world and yet you are still tired?

Welcome to my world...

I have a doctors appointment after school....which means NO SMOKING all day......=( Oh it sucks...

...but it means I am a little closer to cheerleading tryouts!  Yay!

I made this journal so I could write at school.  And suddenly it has been deemed completely innapropriate!  Whatever could I have done?  I mean any of you who know me as well as you do, know that I swear a lot...look at my entries, I RARELY EVER SWEAR!  This angers me to an unxplainable extent.

Well let me tell you about my day so far, in Video Broadcasting we started working on our "Entertainment Broadcast"  oh yes, so long awaited.  SO for the intro, Kyle (editor) had the majority of the staff walk down Main Street...in a slow motion, macho style.  Hah I couldn't do it.  I mean I was thinking Reservior Dogs, they were thinking about some weird award winning movie, that gets ripped off often or something.  So anyway, NO ONE took it seriously, I mean hey...we are the Word staff. =D

I can not wait to see how it turned out, I bet it is great.  Tonight at Late Night...yay!  Haley and the "Soap Opera" crew are going to her house to film their little segment, AKA: The Sterotypical Soap Opera...oh yea, it shall be grand.

I am very tired....yes....very tired...couldn't sleep, too cold...

Well I have wasted enough of your oh so important time, and think I will leave you now, hell I might be back in third hour...Creative Writing, I own that one computer! =D

Later everyone (oh yea the oh so many of you who read this ;) )

I love the smell of matches...

Mr. Baxter has this really good smelling candle lit.  I have late night tonight......if it doesn't snow and lock us all up....

Heh...must skip...must smoke awesome cigarettes George bought me.

Happy Fat Tuesday!  I love Mardi Gras...I am even wearing beads and looking kind of like a vampire...yay!  No flashing people.....sorry. =D

I am so tired, I couldn't sleep last night, I kept hearing people talking, it kind of freaked me out, and when I FINALLY did get to sleep my alarm was ringing.......maybe I am a vampire...;)

Now I gotta go. People need the computer.

I love George.  I know I said I would probably never write stuff like that in here, but I do.  Alright...I am done with that. =D

I hate school.  Watched old episodes of the Word in Journalism today....from like 2001 - 2002 or something like that.  Quite interesting.  I thought they were kind of funny, in a twisted way.

What does this day have planned for me I wonder.

Autumn I love you too!  I only wish that there was something I could do to make you feel better, I don't even know what's wrong.  Well I am here for you as always.

I will write more as my day progresses...if I am lucky.

I am very bored, thank goodness SSR just ended, now I am awaiting for my broadcast to air...I am nervous, I hope it works, and I hope I did a good job. =D

Dad said I could go to the Venue tonight.  Which is good, although I am probably not gonna watch too much of the show, and I need more cigarettes, I wonder if George would buy me some...?

OOOh Winter Royalty nominees...I wonder if people will vote for me.

Rawr!  Screw censorship up it's a$$....(I know I know, but honestly I want to continue writing in here from school)  F-ing rules.

But I mean any of you who actually know me, know that I never edit what I say.  I just do this so that I don't get blocked.

In our Creative Writing class we had to write a five paragraph paper persuading people on a controversial topic.........CENSORSHIP OF THE MEDIA....oh yes, what fun that was.

*gets down off soap box*

Have a great day.

I hate being cold, and I hate having no smokes, especially when I have late night.
I hope George comes to see me, I miss him....Aaron is making up for it though, ;) 

Blah this day is almost over.

Thayer didn't show up until the end of class, so Josh had to go on camera with me.  I suck at being an anchor.  I fell out of my chair and busted my ass, thank god the camera wasn't on.  Although if it was it would have been hilarious! =D

When I was watching Kyle export, I noticed how much of a bitch I actually look like.  I swear if I would you I would probably be afraid of me too.  Sorry if I am rude.  I really don't mean to be.

So on Friday is when the broadcast airs....sadly I am looking forward to it, I think I look really pretty.  Black polka dotted dress and heels never fails. =D

Well I suppose that is all I will bore you people (If infact there is anyone) with for today.

Later.

Monday.  Morning.  Weight Training.  Pain.  Someone kill me.

Now I am in Seminar, bored.  Yes bored.

Can not wait for lunch so I can skip.  Yea, skip.  And yes I know it is bad, kiss my ass.  

Young Democrats after school...yay!~  Yea I know I am a nerd, whatever.  

Well the bell is about to ring for me to go to Video Broadcast, yay!  Write a script and talk to people who don't give a damn, sounds like a plan to me.

I miss my Romeo.  and my notebook. =(

I miss my Romeo...
                  I fucking hate my parents...
*insert scream* 
               I can't even explain the emotion running through my heart...
  the tears falling from my eyes...
                                  and how happy my dagger looks...

I am wearing an angora green sweater...regular blue jeans, tan heels, white earrings, and a diamond watch...that is it.  As for make up I have on lip gloss and mascara.  Painfully normal, simply beautiful.  No one even recognizes me....shocking.  Although I have recieved quite a few compliments.  This whole thing is just weird.

I miss George, and I really need to leave...cause I gotta smoke...turns out Brett and Katy have this lunch too!!!!!! Yeee!! I might be leaving more...whoot whoot!

I am so bad ass I only skip lunch, whoo check me out.

Ugh bored.  Done with Creative Writing work...yay!

Be back later...maybe...

I'm so sick of these people, but I'm too scared to be alone...

~Rise Against!

Oh goodness, something sooooo terrible has happened.....my notebook, the one I carry around EVERYWHERE is gone!  It is filled with things that NO ONE should know, especially if it gets into the wrong hands....oh god...

Autumn I now know how this feels....damn.

Rawr!   F-ing Pioneer Pride assembly.....ugh so boring, I have two tickets, one for Perfect Attendance, and the other for 3.2 or higher GPA...which is a 3.9!  Yay...

Well I am gonna get off now, cause I am angry and worried about my notebook.

A girl asked a guy if he thought she was pretty, 
he said...no. 

She asked him if he would want to be with her forever.... 
and he said no. 

She then asked him if she were to leave would he cry, 
and once again he replied with a no. 

She had heard enough. 
As she walked away, tears streaming down her face 

The boy grabbed her arm and said.... 
You're not pretty you're beautiful. 

I don't want to be with you forever. 
I NEED to be with you forever. 

And I wouldn't cry if you walked away...I'd die...

I got in a fight with my parents...again...

(side note: I would LOVE to kill Andre)

It was about us moving....the end of my Senior year we are moving to mother f-ing Michigan...yes to be with their families...BAAAHHHH!  They said the would ONLY pay for me to go to college if I went in Michigan...ugh...

Autumn I love you, would you want to live with me in my parents house?  There might be a basement we can call our own....=D

Well thats it, and oh yea ROTC is still like a cult. (sorry friends)

You know how I totally despise Valentines Day....because 
1. It is not a real holiday.
2. I am ALWAYS alone
3. What's the freaking point?

Well George somehow has something planned, and I am rather scared.....dun dun dun....sadly I won't see him then either...cause he works...=(  Damn people and their oh so important jobs, which reminds me I need to get one.

HeeHee...Patrick Moran thought I was dating Aaron, Matt, or George...or two of them or whatever.  I corrected him so the world makes sense again. =)

Blah gotta go, soooo bored!

Whoo...that was fun.  Had to let it all out.
Computer Tech with Mrs. Hansen is awesome.  I am all done cause I am a good girl. =D  Yeaaa.

Aaron is listening to his cd player completely drowning out the world, like I am currently.  Occasionally we talk which is kewl I suppose.

Ugh what to say now.

Oh goodness...Coach Hart said, "Word Up!"  Today in class I nearly died laughing.  Then he said we are all just screwing our cousins because some how everyone in this world is related...weird huh?  Then he made the valid point that he is related to us too and I laughed...Coach Hart is god.

Skipped with Brett and Katy...went to Jasmines and saw her get REALLLLY angry.  Poor girl.  Still pretty kewl.

Ugh can't go to the venue forever...mom said it is costing me too much money, when really it doesn't cost me a thing.  One of the many perks of dating George. <3 I love him...he doesn't know that...well in those words atleast.  But I do.  Although my mom and dad are going to beg to differ by trying to keep me from having further relations.  Screw it.

Whoo done for now, gotta piss off some people because we all know that is fun. =D

You are a Kitchen Knife.



You are a very aggressive person, not hesitating to make a fatal move in order to succeed. You are always aware of what is going on around you, though other people aren't. You are over-protective of some of your valued possessions, though you gamble to gain more. If someone gets in your way, you kill them. If you hate someone, they die. Well, not literally. People fear you for your skills and envy your success, but you don't care. You liked to be feared in order to gain reverence. You are the most powerful of all silverware, and cut up peoples souls. I mean food.

Most compatible with: Toothbrush.


Click here -- What Random Object Represents Your Inner Self?

First off in my Anatomy class that Do Do birds evolved into our now known as "xHardXCorex" kids. Interesting huh?

Second many people have told me to stay a virgin as long as possible. 

Intersting facts.

So not of any interest to y'all. But I thought I would mention it.

Well this sucks.  I can not travel in seminar today, and it was rather important, I had to talk to Coach Schmidt.  Now I am talking to Elizabeth about Garden State, we are looking at the website.  Debating whether or not to download a really awesome desktop.  Its of Large and Sam in the airport.  Awww...=)
Blah.  So bored.

Happy New Year!  So yea I finally got to go to the venue...sadly...I wanted to go.  I had a good time, then again I wasn't in the place half the time. =D
I hung out with George, Will, Ali, Casey...and I think thats it.  Ali introduced me to Becky, she seems really sweet.  I saw tons of people, Brett, Jasmine, Jet, Laura, Caleb, Megan, and quite a few more, but those are the few who stopped and had a small conversation with me.

Overall I can say I had a good time, I wasn't home...(as usual) and I got to smoke myself stupid.  Yay!  All is good.  Except this morning when you are rudely awaken by all the lights in the damn basement...that sucks.  You realize you were having this wonderful dream, and only to be awaken in disapointment and sadness.  Damn I miss him.

Well that is all for now.  Ali and I just got off the phone.  I'm spending the night with her, Rachel, and Casey tonight.  Fun stuff.

I can't let her know she's right.
I can't let her know she's right.
I can't let her know she's right.

By the way...my mom is insane and hates me.  Yes she hates me, she said it to me this morning and ya know what...I believe her.

Would you trust me as a teacher?
Cause I get to be one for a day!  At West Middle School.  I get to tell the little kids about the Word.  Fun stuff eh.  I hope they are not little brats...or else I will kill them after school!  =D
Well that will be all for now since I am supposed to be working on a poem, a poem in which I can not do.  Ugh.  Sound poetry sucks!

My childrens book was a hit!  Yay!  You have no idea how happy I am.  Samantha (the little girl) told everyone in her class know how kewl it was.  So yay!
I also got back just in time for lunch!  Whoo! =D
Now I am in computer tech and in a GREAT mood.
Well yea...I might edit this later, but who knows.

My mom found my cigarettes...and you know what, when my dad told me this, I didn't feel angry or anything, I was sad...and really needed a cigarette.  Isn't that terrible?
I love it so much....that when I find out I can't have it...I don't know...I want it more.  I think we call that lust children.  Pure lust.
So whatever I gotta get ready to give a ROTC interview....dun dun dun...oh joy.
=(

Another day of this class...rawr!  It sucks and I am angered.
My dad came home last night.  =D  And he told me that on Saturday since I want to go to the Venue, he will be joining me...oh goodness.  My dad at Groundwork.  Trust me y'all thats a scary thought.  But if it gets me closer to going all by myself then awesome, so for it.  Well bells about to ring and I should go.  Later.

Not the whole class, just a few deserving few....no names, the people know who they are.

Ms. Hansen is by far one of the kewlest teachers in the entire world.  She is so liberal and I love it!  We just got into this discussion about controversy....and how I love to argue with people just to see how they react.  It's great. =D  I am easily amused by the actions of people.  She seems to like my poetry...so yay!  That's awesome, few do.  By the way...any of you who are interested in reading some of my greatest works...www.poetry.com     Type in: Raker (Last Name) Jacquelyn (First Name) and enjoy! =D

So yep...that is my class and my totally awesome computer tech teacher.  You are so lucky if you can get her, I so advise it!

I had this terrible dream last night.  My dad returns home tonight.....

But in my dream his plane crashed...I woke up crying and I couldn't believe it.  Oh I am soooo scared.  I don't want anything to happen to my dad, I love him and would feel so terrible if something did.

...scared out of my mind.

We are under a lock down...dun dun dun....am I a bad girl?
Doubtful...oh so doubtful.
I am tired, possibly RoboTripping...I mean I took some this morning and I think I still have kind of a buzz...or maybe it's a burnout.  Who knows?
SO yea...sitting here talking to my friend Aaron.  He is super kewl.  Goodness I am cold.

"Let me take my clothes off and hug you..."
~Autumn

xoxo...yea talking later.

I am at school.  Fun stuff.  Autumn is here!

"Move bitch! Get out da way..."

"Clearly there is a bitch in his way and he wants her to move."

"Hence "Move bitch get out da way..."

Damn I love that Chris Rock.  He is like freaking god.
